The paper deals with a graph optimization problem and presents an algorithmic approach to solve it. The problem involves finding a subgraph of minimum cost with certain connectivity constraints. This falls under the category of graph algorithms and optimization, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. "cs.DS" (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as it deals with algorithmic approaches to solve graph problems. "cs.DM" (Discrete Mathematics) is also likely as it deals with combinatorial optimization problems. "cs.GT" (Computer Science and Game Theory) is another possibility as it deals with graph theory and optimization problems. "cs.NA" (Numerical Analysis) and "cs.RO" (Robotics) are less likely but still possible as they deal with optimization problems and algorithmic approaches to solve them.
